#Approach:

**Even Reverse – Hinglish Approach**

Is question me hume linked list ke **even position wale nodes ko reverse karna hai**, aur fir unko wapas odd nodes ke beech me same position pattern me lagana hai.

Example:
`1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 4 -> 5`
Even position nodes = `2, 4`
Reverse even = `4, 2`
Final list = `1 -> 4 -> 3 -> 2 -> 5`

---

### Approach used in this code

Is problem ko 3 steps me solve kiya gaya hai:

---

### Step 1: Odd aur Even nodes alag karo

Ek traversal me list ko do lists me split kar diya:

* Odd position list → `1 -> 3 -> 5`
* Even position list → `2 -> 4`

Iske liye:

* `cnt` variable use kiya position track karne ke liye
* `dummyNodeOdd` aur `dummyNodeEven` use kiye list banane ke liye

---

### Step 2: Even list ko reverse karo

Ab even position wali list ko reverse kar diya:

`2 -> 4` becomes `4 -> 2`

Ye normal linked list reverse function se kiya.

---

### Step 3: Odd aur reversed Even list ko merge karo alternately

Ab final step me odd aur reversed even list ko alternate connect kar diya:

* odd ka node
* even ka node
* odd ka next
* even ka next

Isi se final reordered list mil jaati hai.

---

### Example dry run

Input:
`1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 4 -> 5`

After split:

* Odd = `1 -> 3 -> 5`
* Even = `2 -> 4`

Reverse even:

* `4 -> 2`

Merge:

* `1 -> 4 -> 3 -> 2 -> 5`

---

### Important pointer logic

Merge karte time next pointers store karna zaroori hai:

```java
ListNode oddNext = oddptr.next;
ListNode evenNext = evenptr.next;

oddptr.next = evenptr;
evenptr.next = oddNext;
```

Isse links break nahi hote.

---

### Complexity

* **Time Complexity:** `O(n)`
* **Space Complexity:** `O(1)` (sirf pointers use hue hain, extra list nodes nahi banaye)

---

### One-line logic

> Odd aur even nodes alag karo → even list reverse karo → dono ko alternate merge karo.


#Code:

/* class ListNode {
	int val;
	ListNode next;
	ListNode() { val = 0; next = null; }
	ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; next = null; }
	ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }
} */

public class Solution {

    public ListNode reverse(ListNode head){
      if(head == null || head.next == null) return head;

      ListNode temp = head;
      ListNode prev = null;
      while(temp != null){
        ListNode front = temp.next;
        temp.next = prev;
        prev = temp;
        temp = front;
      }
      return prev;
    }

    public ListNode evenReverse(ListNode A) {
      //You can code here
			
      ListNode dummyNodeOdd = new ListNode(-1);
      ListNode dummyNodeEven = new ListNode(-1);

      ListNode odd = dummyNodeOdd;
      ListNode even = dummyNodeEven;
      int cnt = 1;

      ListNode temp = A;
      while(temp != null){
        //if temp is at odd place
        if(cnt % 2 == 1){
          odd.next = temp;
          odd = odd.next;
        }
        //if temp is at even place
        else{
          even.next = temp;
          even = even.next;
        }
        temp = temp.next;
        cnt++;
      }
      odd.next = null;
      even.next = null;
      //Reverse even LL
      ListNode evenHead = reverse(dummyNodeEven.next);
      ListNode oddHead = dummyNodeOdd.next;

      ListNode res = oddHead;
      ListNode evenptr = evenHead;
      ListNode oddptr = oddHead;
      while(oddptr != null && evenptr != null){
        ListNode oddNext = oddptr.next;
        ListNode evenNext = evenptr.next;

        oddptr.next = evenptr;
        evenptr.next = oddNext;

        oddptr = oddNext;
        evenptr = evenNext;

      }
      return res;      
    }
}
